<div id="contentR">
<h2>Delta Tau</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.deltatau.com/common/sales/distributorsandintegrators.asp?connectionstr=release&amp;searchbystate=51" target="_blank">Delta Tau Data Systems, Inc</a>
has included Nova Systems on their list of preferred systems
integrators. This achievement was a combination of demonstrated ability
to work with the PMAC software environment and the successful completion
of motion projects. Watch for more information concerning the new Linux based Power PMAC motion controller.
</p>
<h2>MAAG Gear Shaper</h2>
<p>Nova Systems has completed a 7th full
MAAG retrofit and many other RAM drive upgrades to SH-250, SH-450 and SH-600 Gear Shapers. For more information and video, see the MAAG Gear Shaper Case Study on our <a href="technologies.html#motion"> Motion Control</a> page.
</p>
<h2>Baldor</h2>
<p>
<a href="http://www.baldor.com/default.asp" target="_blank">Baldor Electric Company</a> has designated Nova Systems
as both a Motion Integrator and
a Drives Integrator.  In this capacity, Nova Systems is Factory Authorized to handle applications,
start-ups and warranties on all Baldor VFD and Servo products.  Contact us to find out
how to receive extended factory warranty on new VFD installations.
</p>
<h2>CSIA</h2>
<p>Nova Systems is a member of the
<a href="http://www.controlsys.org" target="_blank">Control Systems Integrators
Association,</a> an international organization that promotes integration
excellence. Initial certification was obtained by passing an audit
conducted by a 3rd party examiner in 2004.  Recertification occurred in
2007, 2010 and 2013.
</p>
<a href="http://www.controlsys.org" target="_blank"><img class="vspace" alt="CSIA" src="images/csia_nova.jpg" /></a>
